Class LogicBlock

  • java.lang.Object
    • LogicBlock
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActionLogicBlock, AndLogicBlock, OrLogicBlock, TriggerLogicBlock

    public abstract class LogicBlock
extends java.lang.Object
    A LogicBlock represents one piece of the logical representation of a Service in the system.

    A LogicBlock contains a list of prevBlocks and nextBlocks.

    A LogicBlock has a boolean output value that is determined by the update method to be implemented in subclasses of LogicBlock.

    Each LogicBlock also contains an int, numServices, that reflects the number of Service objects making use of this LogicBlock.

    Author:
    Shawn Koop

      • removeFromService

        public void removeFromService()
        Removes this LogicBlock from a service, decrementing numServices.

        If numServices was 1, then this LogicBlock is removed from the nextBlocks list of all LogicBlock objects in prevBlocks and from the prevBlocks list of all LogicBlock objects in nextBlocks. This LogicBlock will have been removed from the system since it is no longer used by any services.
